  "prompt": "Which phone is best to buy under 17000 rs?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, there are several good smartphones available in India under \u20b917,000. Here are some popular options you might consider:\n\n1. **Realme Narzo 50**:\n   - **Display**: 6.6-inch FHD+ display\n   - **Processor**: MediaTek Helio G96\n   - **RAM/Storage**: Up to 6GB RAM and up to 128GB storage\n   - **Camera**: 50MP triple camera setup\n   - **Battery**: 5000mAh with fast charging\n\n2. **Xiaomi Redmi Note 11**:\n   - **Display**: 6.43-inch FHD+ AMOLED display\n   - **Processor**: Snapdragon 680\n   - **RAM/Storage**: Up to 6GB RAM and up to 128GB storage\n   - **Camera**: 50MP quad-camera setup\n   - **Battery**: 5000mAh with 33W fast charging\n\n3. **Samsung Galaxy M32**:\n   - **Display**: 6.4-inch FHD+ Super AMOLED display\n   - **Processor**: MediaTek Helio G80\n   - **RAM/Storage**: Up to 6GB RAM and 128GB storage\n   - **Camera**: 64MP quad-camera setup\n   - **Battery**: 6000mAh battery with 15W charging\n\n4. **Poco M4 Pro**:\n   - **Display**: 6.43-inch FHD+ AMOLED display\n   - **Processor**: MediaTek Dimensity 810\n   - **RAM/Storage**: Up to 6GB RAM and 128GB storage\n   - **Camera**: 64MP triple camera\n   - **Battery**: 5000mAh with 33W fast charging\n\n5. **Vivo T1 5G**:\n   - **Display**: 6.58-inch FHD+ display\n   - **Processor**: Snapdragon 695\n   - **RAM/Storage**: Up to 8GB RAM and 128GB storage\n   - **Camera**: 50MP triple camera setup\n   - **Battery**: 5000mAh with 18W charging\n\nWhen choosing a phone, consider factors such as camera quality, battery life, software experience, and brand reliability. Prices may vary, and it's advisable to check for current offers or discounts before making a purchase.",
